Banana Oat Pancakes
fields.instructions:
Mash the banana in a bowl.

Add the eggs and oats. Mix well.

Pour small amounts onto a non-stick pan. Cook on medium heat for 2�3 mins per side.

Serve with honey or fruit.

fields.name: Egg & Toast
fields.instructions:
Toast the bread.

Fry or scramble the eggs in a little butter/oil.

Season with salt and pepper, serve on toast.

fields.name: Tuna Salad Sandwich
fields.instructions:
Drain the tuna and mix with mayo.

Spread on bread. Add lettuce if available.

Serve as a sandwich.

fields.name: Simple Rice Bowl
fields.instructions:
Cook the egg (scrambled or fried).

Heat rice and veggies together in a pan or microwave.

Add soy sauce and top with the egg.

fields.name: Baked Chicken & Potatoes
fields.instructions:
Chop potatoes, place with chicken in a baking dish.

Drizzle with oil, season, and bake at 200�C (400�F) for 30�40 mins.

Flip halfway through if needed.

fields.name: Pasta with Tomato Sauce
fields.instructions:
Boil pasta.

In a pan, heat oil, add tomatoes (and garlic/onion if using). Simmer 10 mins.

Drain pasta, mix with sauce.

fields.name: Chicken Breast with Roasted Potatoes
fields.instructions:
Chicken Breast:

Rub chicken with olive oil, salt, pepper, and paprika.

Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat.

Cook chicken for 5�6 minutes per side or until cooked through (internal temp 75�C).

Rest for 3 minutes before slicing. Add lemon juice if desired.

Roasted Potatoes:

Preheat oven to 200�C (390�F).

Cut potatoes into small wedges or cubes.

Toss with olive oil, salt, and rosemary.

Bake on a tray for 25�30 minutes, flipping halfway, until golden and crispy.
